# Markdown formatting

Follow the [Consensys Markdown formatting guide](https://docs-template.consensys.net/contribute/format-markdown)
for full details.
The rules below cover common conventions in this repository.

## Line length and sentence breaks

- Wrap lines at roughly 80 columns.
- Start each new sentence on a new line to keep diffs readable.

## Links

- Use relative links for pages.
- Use descriptive link text.

## Code blocks

- Always add language tags to fenced code blocks.
- Keep examples copy-paste ready.
- Do not include shell prompts in commands.
- Use angle-bracket placeholders for user-provided values.

## Tabs

- Use Docusaurus `<Tabs>` and `<TabItem>` for parallel examples.
- Import `Tabs` and `TabItem` when required by the page.

## Admonitions

- Use Docusaurus admonitions (`:::note`, `:::tip`, `:::warning`, and related types).
- Add a custom title only when it improves scanability.
- Do not nest admonitions.

## Frontmatter

- Required: `description` (single sentence).
- Recommended: `keywords`.
- `sidebar_label` is optional and should only be used when the default nav label is too long.
- If frontmatter includes a `title`, avoid adding a duplicate H1 in page content.

## File and folder names

- Use lowercase and dashes only.

## Diagrams

- Use Mermaid where diagrams are needed and the page already follows that pattern.
